                <text x="830" y="74" fill="rgba(239,68,68,0.95)" font-size="24" font-family="ui-mono, monospace" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">~12 hrs</text>
                <text x="830" y="96" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">avg. resolution latency</text>

                <!-- Divider -->
                <line x1="0" y1="152" x2="1060" y2="152" stroke="rgba(100,116,139,0.2)" stroke-width="1"></line>

                <!-- AFTER label -->
                <text x="20" y="176" fill="rgba(59,130,246,0.9)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif, system-ui" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="3">AFTER APEX</text>
                <text x="20" y="194" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="11" font-family="ui-sans-serif">Automated pipeline - under 30 seconds</text>

                <!-- After step boxes -->
                <rect x="20" y="205" width="120" height="50" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,40,0.8)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="80" y="228" fill="rgba(147,197,253,0.95)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">Detection</text>
                <text x="80" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">any site</text>
                <line x1="140" y1="230" x2="168" y2="230" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.7)" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr-blue)"></line>

                <rect x="168" y="205" width="120" height="50" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,40,0.8)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="228" y="228" fill="rgba(147,197,253,0.95)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">Auto-Normalize</text>
                <text x="228" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">schema mapped</text>
                <line x1="288" y1="230" x2="316" y2="230" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.7)" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr-blue)"></line>

                <rect x="316" y="205" width="120" height="50" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,40,0.8)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="376" y="228" fill="rgba(147,197,253,0.95)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">KPI + Diagnose</text>
                <text x="376" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">AI-computed</text>
                <line x1="436" y1="230" x2="464" y2="230" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.7)" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr-blue)"></line>

                <rect x="464" y="205" width="120" height="50" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,40,0.8)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="524" y="228" fill="rgba(147,197,253,0.95)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">Structured Brief</text>
                <text x="524" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">auto-generated</text>
                <line x1="584" y1="230" x2="612" y2="230" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.7)" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr-blue)"></line>

                <rect x="612" y="205" width="120" height="50" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,40,0.8)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.45)" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text x="672" y="228" fill="rgba(147,197,253,0.95)" font-size="12" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">Decision</text>
                <text x="672" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">seconds later</text>

                <!-- <30s callout -->
                <rect x="760" y="198" width="140" height="64" rx="10" fill="rgba(10,20,50,0.6)" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.4)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
                <text x="830" y="224" fill="rgba(59,130,246,0.95)" font-size="24" font-family="ui-mono, monospace" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">&lt;30 sec</text>
                <text x="830" y="246" fill="rgba(148,163,184,0.6)" font-size="10" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">data-to-briefing pipeline</text>

                <!-- Footer note -->
                <text x="530" y="296" fill="rgba(100,116,139,0.65)" font-size="11" font-family="ui-sans-serif" text-anchor="middle">APEX does not automate engineering judgment. It eliminates the manual assembly step that delays it.</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- PROBLEM LANDSCAPE -->
        <section class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-500">Problem Landscape</p>
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            The problems APEX addresses were not stated directly. They were inferred from three overlapping signals:
            a direct conversation with Amkor's process team, patterns embedded in concurrent internship postings,
            and the structural realities of operating a global OSAT at advanced packaging complexity.
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-red-900/50 bg-red-950/10 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-300">Downtime Resolution Latency</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Equipment failures trigger a manual chain: detect → email → call → pull data from multiple systems → diagnose → act. Across global time zones, this averages up to 12 hours. The bottleneck is not the repair. It is the information routing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-900/40 bg-amber-950/10 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-300">Fragmented Operational Data</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Factories across Korea, Japan, Vietnam, and Portugal likely operate different MES systems with different fault code schemas and yield formats. Corporate receives summarized spreadsheets, not structured feeds. No unified semantic layer exists.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-amber-900/40 bg-amber-950/10 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-400"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-300">Manual Reporting Cycle</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Product managers and engineers spend hours each week pulling data from disparate systems, consolidating into Excel, and building PowerPoint decks for leadership review. The intern postings explicitly describe this as a core workload. It is high-effort, low-value work.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-orange-900/40 bg-orange-950/10 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-orange-400"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-orange-300">Profitability Visibility Lag</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Product-level profitability requires joining ERP cost data, production actuals, and pricing structures, all done manually. Margin reporting is periodic and retrospective. Erosion can go undetected for weeks before surfacing in a review cycle.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/40 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200">Pricing and Allocation Misalignment</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Pricing decisions across business units are made without a unified view of factory capacity, tool utilization, or real-time cost structure. Volume allocation lags actual equipment loading. Decisions are made from spreadsheets that are already stale.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/40 p-5 space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200">Executive Reporting Friction</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Every intern posting requires a final deliverable: a presentation with recommendations. This mirrors what product engineers do continuously. The organization's primary internal communication artifact is a manually built PowerPoint deck assembled every review cycle.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- NEEDS DISCOVERY -->
        <section class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-500">Needs Discovery</p>
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Organizations in operational transformation rarely state their needs precisely. The stated need and the actual need
            are different layers. APEX was designed by working through three layers of signal simultaneously.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-blue-900/40 bg-blue-950/10 p-5 space-y-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-300 uppercase tracking-widest">Explicit Needs - Directly Stated</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Source: direct conversation with Drake Miller, Amkor Process Team</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-300">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Faster downtime triage - reduce the 12-hour resolution window</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>An AI solution that takes in raw factory data and processes it automatically</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Converts data into a presentation or dashboard with explanations of what changed</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Explains what changed and what actions are needed, without manual assembly</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-violet-900/40 bg-violet-950/10 p-5 space-y-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-violet-300 uppercase tracking-widest">Inferred Needs - Extracted from Posting Language</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Source: three concurrent Product Engineer Intern postings, cross-referenced for repeated themes</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-300">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Automation of pricing strategy analysis across customer and package type</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>CapEx planning support and factory operating efficiency monitoring</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Product profitability monitoring using Copilot and LLM tools</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Consolidation of product overview presentations and factory capability summaries</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Volume allocation and equipment utilization optimization</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span>Agentic AI, Microsoft Copilot, and Power Automate are mentioned directly, not scoped</span></li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 pt-1 italic">
                The simultaneous mention of Excel/VBA and Agentic AI in the same posting is the diagnostic signal.
                It describes a manual workflow the organization wants to automate but has not yet decomposed into its actual failure modes.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-900/40 bg-emerald-950/10 p-5 space-y-3">
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-300 uppercase tracking-widest">Implicit Needs - Structurally Inferred</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500">Source: OSAT industry operating model, global factory complexity, IP sensitivity</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-300">
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span><span class="font-medium text-gray-200">Data privacy and IP protection</span>: Amkor handles customer designs under strict NDA. Any AI system must default to local inference with no external data egress.</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span><span class="font-medium text-gray-200">Auditability</span>: Recommendations must show their work. Black-box AI outputs are not acceptable in a manufacturing environment where decisions affect yield, quality, and customer commitments.</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span><span class="font-medium text-gray-200">Repeatability</span>: Reporting must be structurally consistent across sites and over time. One-off dashboards are not trusted operationally.</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span><span class="font-medium text-gray-200">Change management compatibility</span>: The system must fit into existing workflows rather than requiring engineers to abandon their current process entirely.</span></li>
                <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">→</span><span><span class="font-medium text-gray-200">Cross-factory normalization</span>: Different facilities run different MES systems with different fault code schemas. Before any intelligence layer can work, raw data must be harmonized. This is the foundational prerequisite most AI implementations skip.</span></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SYSTEM VISION -->
        <section class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-500">System Vision</p>
            <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-slate-800"></div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            APEX is not a dashboard. It is a <span class="text-blue-400 font-medium">decision pipeline</span>.
            A dashboard presents data. A decision pipeline converts data into a structured, actionable briefing
            without requiring a human to assemble it. The full vision is a cross-factory operational intelligence layer,
            a system connecting factory signals to corporate decisions across the entire global footprint.
          </p>

          <!-- Layered Architecture Diagram -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/60 p-5">
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest">System Architecture - Data to Executive Action</p>
            <div class="w-full overflow-x-auto">
